102 case MVT::v4i8: ----
103 Opcode = IsValidInc ? Hexagon::L2_loadri_pi : Hexagon::L2_loadri_io; 0
104 break; 0
105 case MVT::i64: 0
106 case MVT::f64: ----
107 case MVT::v2i32: ----
108 case MVT::v4i16: ----
109 case MVT::v8i8: ----

111 break; 0

141 Zero, SDValue(N, 0)); 0

148 ----
149 // Loaded value Next address Chain ----

221 SDNode *HexagonDAGToDAGISel::StoreInstrForLoadIntrinsic(MachineSDNode *LoadN, 0
222 SDNode *IntN) { ----
223 // The "LoadN" is just a machine load instruction. The intrinsic also ----
224 // involves storing it. Generate an appropriate store to the location ----
225 // given in the intrinsic's operand(3). ----
226 uint64_t F = HII->get(LoadN->getMachineOpcode()).TSFlags; 0
227 unsigned SizeBits = (F >> HexagonII::MemAccessSizePos) & 0
228 HexagonII::MemAccesSizeMask; ----
229 unsigned Size = 1U << (SizeBits-1); 0
230 ----
231 SDLoc dl(IntN); 0
232 MachinePointerInfo PI; 0
233 SDValue TS; 0
234 SDValue Loc = IntN->getOperand(3); 0
235 ----
236 if (Size >= 4) 0
237 TS = CurDAG->getStore(SDValue(LoadN, 2), dl, SDValue(LoadN, 0), Loc, PI, 0
238 Align(Size)); ----
239 else ----
240 TS = CurDAG->getTruncStore(SDValue(LoadN, 2), dl, SDValue(LoadN, 0), Loc, 0
241 PI, MVT::getIntegerVT(Size * 8), Align(Size)); ----
242 ----
243 SDNode *StoreN; ----
244 { ----
245 HandleSDNode Handle(TS); 0
246 SelectStore(TS.getNode()); 0
247 StoreN = Handle.getValue().getNode(); 0
248 } 0
249 ----
250 // Load's results are { Loaded value, Updated pointer, Chain } ----
251 ReplaceUses(SDValue(IntN, 0), SDValue(LoadN, 1)); 0
252 ReplaceUses(SDValue(IntN, 1), SDValue(StoreN, 0)); 0
253 return StoreN; 0
254 } 0
255 ----
256 bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::tryLoadOfLoadIntrinsic(LoadSDNode *N) { 0
257 // The intrinsics for load circ/brev perform two operations: ----
258 // 1. Load a value V from the specified location, using the addressing ----
259 // mode corresponding to the intrinsic. ----
260 // 2. Store V into a specified location. This location is typically a ----
261 // local, temporary object. ----
262 // In many cases, the program using these intrinsics will immediately ----
263 // load V again from the local object. In those cases, when certain ----
264 // conditions are met, the last load can be removed. ----
265 // This function identifies and optimizes this pattern. If the pattern ----
266 // cannot be optimized, it returns nullptr, which will cause the load ----
267 // to be selected separately from the intrinsic (which will be handled ----
268 // in SelectIntrinsicWChain). ----
269 ----
270 SDValue Ch = N->getOperand(0); 0
271 SDValue Loc = N->getOperand(1); 0
272 ----
273 // Assume that the load and the intrinsic are connected directly with a ----
274 // chain: ----
275 // t1: i32,ch = int.load ..., ..., ..., Loc, ... // <-- C ----
276 // t2: i32,ch = load t1:1, Loc, ... ----
277 SDNode *C = Ch.getNode(); 0
278 ----
279 if (C->getOpcode() != ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN) 0
280 return false; 0
281 ----
282 // The second load can only be eliminated if its extension type matches ----
283 // that of the load instruction corresponding to the intrinsic. The user ----
284 // can provide an address of an unsigned variable to store the result of ----
285 // a sign-extending intrinsic into (or the other way around). ----
286 ISD::LoadExtType IntExt; ----
287 switch (cast(C->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue()) { 0
288 case Intrinsic::hexagon_circ_ldub: 0
289 case Intrinsic::hexagon_circ_lduh: ----
290 IntExt = ISD::ZEXTLOAD; 0
291 break; 0
292 case Intrinsic::hexagon_circ_ldw: 0
293 case Intrinsic::hexagon_circ_ldd: ----
294 IntExt = ISD::NON_EXTLOAD; 0
295 break; 0
296 default: 0
297 IntExt = ISD::SEXTLOAD; 0
298 break; 0
299 } ----
300 if (N->getExtensionType() != IntExt) 0
301 return false; 0
302 ----
303 // Make sure the target location for the loaded value in the load intrinsic ----
304 // is the location from which LD (or N) is loading. ----
305 if (C->getNumOperands() < 4 || Loc.getNode() != C->getOperand(3).getNode()) 0
306 return false; 0
307 ----
308 if (MachineSDNode *L = LoadInstrForLoadIntrinsic(C)) { 0
309 SDNode *S = StoreInstrForLoadIntrinsic(L, C); 0
310 SDValue F[] = { SDValue(N,0), SDValue(N,1), SDValue(C,0), SDValue(C,1) }; 0
311 SDValue T[] = { SDValue(L,0), SDValue(S,0), SDValue(L,1), SDValue(S,0) }; 0
312 ReplaceUses(F, T, std::size(T)); 0
313 // This transformation will leave the intrinsic dead. If it remains in ----
314 // the DAG, the selection code will see it again, but without the load, ----
315 // and it will generate a store that is normally required for it. ----
316 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(C); 0
317 return true; 0
318 } ----
319 return false; 0
320 } ----

322 // Convert the bit-reverse load intrinsic to appropriate target instruction. ----
323 bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectBrevLdIntrinsic(SDNode *IntN) { 0
324 if (IntN->getOpcode() != ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN) 0
325 return false; 0
326 ----
327 const SDLoc &dl(IntN); 0
328 unsigned IntNo = cast(IntN->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue(); 0
329 ----
330 static const std::map LoadBrevMap = { ----
331 { Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrb_pbr, Hexagon::L2_loadrb_pbr }, ----
332 { Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrub_pbr, Hexagon::L2_loadrub_pbr }, ----
333 { Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrh_pbr, Hexagon::L2_loadrh_pbr }, ----
334 { Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadruh_pbr, Hexagon::L2_loadruh_pbr }, ----
335 { Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadri_pbr, Hexagon::L2_loadri_pbr }, ----
336 { Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrd_pbr, Hexagon::L2_loadrd_pbr } ----
337 }; 0
338 auto FLI = LoadBrevMap.find(IntNo); 0
339 if (FLI != LoadBrevMap.end()) { 0
340 EVT ValTy = ----
341 (IntNo == Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrd_pbr) ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32; 0
342 EVT RTys[] = { ValTy, MVT::i32, MVT::Other }; 0
343 // Operands of Intrinsic: {chain, enum ID of intrinsic, baseptr, ----
344 // modifier}. ----
345 // Operands of target instruction: { Base, Modifier, Chain }. ----
346 MachineSDNode *Res = CurDAG->getMachineNode( 0
347 FLI->second, dl, RTys, 0
348 {IntN->getOperand(2), IntN->getOperand(3), IntN->getOperand(0)}); 0
349 ----
350 MachineMemOperand *MemOp = cast(IntN)->getMemOperand(); 0
351 CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(Res, {MemOp}); 0
352 ----
353 ReplaceUses(SDValue(IntN, 0), SDValue(Res, 0)); 0
354 ReplaceUses(SDValue(IntN, 1), SDValue(Res, 1)); 0
355 ReplaceUses(SDValue(IntN, 2), SDValue(Res, 2)); 0
356 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(IntN); 0
357 return true; 0
358 } ----
359 return false; 0
360 } 0

363 /// The new versions use a CSx register instead of the K field. ----
364 bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectNewCircIntrinsic(SDNode *IntN) { 0
365 if (IntN->getOpcode() != ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN) 0

403 Ops = { IntN->getOperand(2), IntN->getOperand(3), IntN->getOperand(4), 0

405 MachineSDNode *Res = CurDAG->getMachineNode(FLI->second, DL, RTys, Ops); 0
406 ReplaceUses(SDValue(IntN, 0), SDValue(Res, 0)); 0
407 ReplaceUses(SDValue(IntN, 1), SDValue(Res, 1)); 0
408 ReplaceUses(SDValue(IntN, 2), SDValue(Res, 2)); 0
409 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(IntN); 0
410 return true; 0
411 } ----
412 ----
413 static std::map StoreNPcMap = { ----
414 { Intrinsic::hexagon_S2_storerb_pci, Hexagon::PS_storerb_pci }, ----
415 { Intrinsic::hexagon_S2_storerh_pci, Hexagon::PS_storerh_pci }, ----

450 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectLoad(SDNode *N) { 0
451 SDLoc dl(N); 0
452 LoadSDNode *LD = cast(N); 0
453 ----
454 // Handle indexed loads. ----
455 ISD::MemIndexedMode AM = LD->getAddressingMode(); 0
456 if (AM != ISD::UNINDEXED) { 0
457 SelectIndexedLoad(LD, dl); 0
458 return; 0
459 } ----
460 ----
461 // Handle patterns using circ/brev load intrinsics. ----
462 if (tryLoadOfLoadIntrinsic(LD)) 0
463 return; 0
464 ----
465 SelectCode(LD); 0
466 } 0

468 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectIndexedStore(StoreSDNode *ST, const SDLoc &dl) { 0
469 SDValue Chain = ST->getChain(); 0
470 SDValue Base = ST->getBasePtr(); 0
471 SDValue Offset = ST->getOffset(); 0
472 SDValue Value = ST->getValue(); 0
473 // Get the constant value. ----
474 int32_t Inc = cast(Offset.getNode())->getSExtValue(); 0
475 EVT StoredVT = ST->getMemoryVT(); 0
476 EVT ValueVT = Value.getValueType(); 0
477 ----
478 bool IsValidInc = HII->isValidAutoIncImm(StoredVT, Inc); 0
479 unsigned Opcode = 0; 0
480 ----
481 assert(StoredVT.isSimple()); 0
482 switch (StoredVT.getSimpleVT().SimpleTy) { 0
483 case MVT::i8: 0
484 Opcode = IsValidInc ? Hexagon::S2_storerb_pi : Hexagon::S2_storerb_io; 0
485 break; 0
486 case MVT::i16: 0
487 Opcode = IsValidInc ? Hexagon::S2_storerh_pi : Hexagon::S2_storerh_io; 0
488 break; 0
489 case MVT::i32: 0
490 case MVT::f32: ----
491 case MVT::v2i16: ----
492 case MVT::v4i8: ----
493 Opcode = IsValidInc ? Hexagon::S2_storeri_pi : Hexagon::S2_storeri_io; 0
494 break; 0
495 case MVT::i64: 0
496 case MVT::f64: ----
497 case MVT::v2i32: ----
498 case MVT::v4i16: ----
499 case MVT::v8i8: ----
500 Opcode = IsValidInc ? Hexagon::S2_storerd_pi : Hexagon::S2_storerd_io; 0
501 break; 0
502 case MVT::v64i8: 0
503 case MVT::v32i16: ----
504 case MVT::v16i32: ----
505 case MVT::v8i64: ----
506 case MVT::v128i8: ----
507 case MVT::v64i16: ----
508 case MVT::v32i32: ----
509 case MVT::v16i64: ----
510 if (isAlignedMemNode(ST)) { 0
511 if (ST->isNonTemporal()) 0
512 Opcode = IsValidInc ? Hexagon::V6_vS32b_nt_pi : Hexagon::V6_vS32b_nt_ai; 0
513 else ----
514 Opcode = IsValidInc ? Hexagon::V6_vS32b_pi : Hexagon::V6_vS32b_ai; 0
515 } else { ----
516 Opcode = IsValidInc ? Hexagon::V6_vS32Ub_pi : Hexagon::V6_vS32Ub_ai; 0
517 } ----
518 break; 0
519 default: 0
520 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected memory type in indexed store"); 0
521 } ----
522 ----
523 if (ST->isTruncatingStore() && ValueVT.getSizeInBits() == 64) { 0
524 assert(StoredVT.getSizeInBits() < 64 && "Not a truncating store"); 0
525 Value = CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(Hexagon::isub_lo, 0
526 dl, MVT::i32, Value); ----
527 } ----
528 ----
529 SDValue IncV = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Inc, dl, MVT::i32); 0
530 MachineMemOperand *MemOp = ST->getMemOperand(); 0
531 ----
532 // Next address Chain ----
533 SDValue From[2] = { SDValue(ST,0), SDValue(ST,1) }; 0
534 SDValue To[2]; 0
535 ----
536 if (IsValidInc) { 0
537 // Build post increment store. ----
538 SDValue Ops[] = { Base, IncV, Value, Chain }; 0
539 MachineSDNode *S = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opcode, dl, MVT::i32, MVT::Other, 0
540 Ops); ----
541 CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(S, {MemOp}); 0
542 To[0] = SDValue(S, 0); 0
543 To[1] = SDValue(S, 1); 0
544 } else { ----
545 SDValue Zero = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, dl, MVT::i32); 0
546 SDValue Ops[] = { Base, Zero, Value, Chain }; 0
547 MachineSDNode *S = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opcode, dl, MVT::Other, Ops); 0
548 CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(S, {MemOp}); 0
549 To[1] = SDValue(S, 0); 0
550 MachineSDNode *A = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Hexagon::A2_addi, dl, MVT::i32, 0
551 Base, IncV); ----
552 To[0] = SDValue(A, 0); 0
553 } ----
554 ----
555 ReplaceUses(From, To, 2); 0
556 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(ST); 0
557 } 0
558 ----
559 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectStore(SDNode *N) { 0
560 SDLoc dl(N); 0
561 StoreSDNode *ST = cast(N); 0
562 ----
563 // Handle indexed stores. ----
564 ISD::MemIndexedMode AM = ST->getAddressingMode(); 0
565 if (AM != ISD::UNINDEXED) { 0
566 SelectIndexedStore(ST, dl); 0
567 return; 0
568 } ----
569 ----
570 SelectCode(ST); 0
571 } 0
572 ----
573 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectSHL(SDNode *N) { 0
574 SDLoc dl(N); 0
575 SDValue Shl_0 = N->getOperand(0); 0
576 SDValue Shl_1 = N->getOperand(1); 0
577 ----
578 auto Default = [this,N] () -> void { SelectCode(N); }; 0
579 ----
580 if (N->getValueType(0) != MVT::i32 || Shl_1.getOpcode() != ISD::Constant) 0
581 return Default(); 0
582 ----
583 // RHS is const. ----
584 int32_t ShlConst = cast(Shl_1)->getSExtValue(); 0
585 ----
586 if (Shl_0.getOpcode() == ISD::MUL) { 0
587 SDValue Mul_0 = Shl_0.getOperand(0); // Val 0
588 SDValue Mul_1 = Shl_0.getOperand(1); // Const 0
589 // RHS of mul is const. ----
590 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(Mul_1)) { 0
591 int32_t ValConst = C->getSExtValue() << ShlConst; 0
592 if (isInt<9>(ValConst)) { 0
593 SDValue Val = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ValConst, dl, MVT::i32); 0
594 SDNode *Result = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Hexagon::M2_mpysmi, dl, 0
595 MVT::i32, Mul_0, Val); ----
596 ReplaceNode(N, Result); 0
597 return; 0
598 } ----
599 } ----
600 return Default(); 0
601 } ----
602 ----
603 if (Shl_0.getOpcode() == ISD::SUB) { 0
604 SDValue Sub_0 = Shl_0.getOperand(0); // Const 0 0
605 SDValue Sub_1 = Shl_0.getOperand(1); // Val 0
606 if (ConstantSDNode *C1 = dyn_cast(Sub_0)) { 0
607 if (C1->getSExtValue() != 0 || Sub_1.getOpcode() != ISD::SHL) 0
608 return Default(); 0
609 SDValue Shl2_0 = Sub_1.getOperand(0); // Val 0
610 SDValue Shl2_1 = Sub_1.getOperand(1); // Const 0
611 if (ConstantSDNode *C2 = dyn_cast(Shl2_1)) { 0
612 int32_t ValConst = 1 << (ShlConst + C2->getSExtValue()); 0
613 if (isInt<9>(-ValConst)) { 0
614 SDValue Val = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(-ValConst, dl, MVT::i32); 0
615 SDNode *Result = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Hexagon::M2_mpysmi, dl, 0
616 MVT::i32, Shl2_0, Val); ----
617 ReplaceNode(N, Result); 0
618 return; 0
619 } ----
620 } ----
621 } ----
622 } ----
623 ----
624 return Default(); 0
625 } 0
626 ----
627 // ----
628 // Handling intrinsics for circular load and bitreverse load. ----
629 // ----
630 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectIntrinsicWChain(SDNode *N) { 0
631 if (MachineSDNode *L = LoadInstrForLoadIntrinsic(N)) { 0
632 StoreInstrForLoadIntrinsic(L, N); 0
633 CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(N); 0
634 return; 0
635 } ----
636 ----
637 // Handle bit-reverse load intrinsics. ----
638 if (SelectBrevLdIntrinsic(N)) 0
639 return; 0
640 ----
641 if (SelectNewCircIntrinsic(N)) 0
642 return; 0
643 ----
644 unsigned IntNo = cast(N->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue(); 0
645 if (IntNo == Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermw || 0
646 IntNo == Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermw_128B || 0
647 IntNo == Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermh || 0
648 IntNo == Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermh_128B || 0
649 IntNo == Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermhw || 0
650 IntNo == Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermhw_128B) { ----
651 SelectV65Gather(N); 0
652 return; 0
653 } ----
654 if (IntNo == Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermwq || 0
655 IntNo == Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermwq_128B || 0
656 IntNo == Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermhq || 0
657 IntNo == Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermhq_128B || 0
658 IntNo == Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermhwq || 0
659 IntNo == Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermhwq_128B) { ----
660 SelectV65GatherPred(N); 0
661 return; 0
662 } ----
663 ----
664 SelectCode(N); 0
665 } ----
666 ----
667 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectIntrinsicWOChain(SDNode *N) { 0
668 unsigned IID = cast(N->getOperand(0))->getZExtValue(); 0
669 unsigned Bits; ----
670 switch (IID) { 0
671 case Intrinsic::hexagon_S2_vsplatrb: 0
672 Bits = 8; 0
673 break; 0
674 case Intrinsic::hexagon_S2_vsplatrh: 0
675 Bits = 16; 0
676 break; 0
677 case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vaddcarry: 0
678 case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vaddcarry_128B: ----
679 case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vsubcarry: ----
680 case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vsubcarry_128B: ----
681 SelectHVXDualOutput(N); 0
682 return; 0
683 default: 0
684 SelectCode(N); 0
685 return; 0
686 } ----
687 ----
688 SDValue V = N->getOperand(1); 0
689 SDValue U; 0
690 // Splat intrinsics. ----
691 if (keepsLowBits(V, Bits, U)) { 0
692 SDValue R = CurDAG->getNode(N->getOpcode(), SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0), 0
693 N->getOperand(0), U); 0
694 ReplaceNode(N, R.getNode()); 0
695 SelectCode(R.getNode()); 0
696 return; 0
697 } ----
698 SelectCode(N); 0
699 } ----
700 ----
701 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectExtractSubvector(SDNode *N) { 0
702 SDValue Inp = N->getOperand(0); 0
703 MVT ResTy = N->getValueType(0).getSimpleVT(); 0
704 auto IdxN = cast(N->getOperand(1)); 0
705 unsigned Idx = IdxN->getZExtValue(); 0
706 ----
707 [[maybe_unused]] MVT InpTy = Inp.getValueType().getSimpleVT(); 0
708 [[maybe_unused]] unsigned ResLen = ResTy.getVectorNumElements(); 0
709 assert(InpTy.getVectorElementType() == ResTy.getVectorElementType()); 0
710 assert(2 * ResLen == InpTy.getVectorNumElements()); 0
711 assert(ResTy.getSizeInBits() == 32); 0
712 assert(Idx == 0 || Idx == ResLen); 0
713 ----
714 unsigned SubReg = Idx == 0 ? Hexagon::isub_lo : Hexagon::isub_hi; 0
715 SDValue Ext = CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(SubReg, SDLoc(N), ResTy, Inp); 0
716 ----
717 ReplaceNode(N, Ext.getNode()); 0
718 } 0

757 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectFrameIndex(SDNode *N) { 0
758 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF->getFrameInfo(); 0
759 const HexagonFrameLowering *HFI = HST->getFrameLowering(); 0
760 int FX = cast(N)->getIndex(); 0
761 Align StkA = HFI->getStackAlign(); 0
762 Align MaxA = MFI.getMaxAlign(); 0
763 SDValue FI = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(FX, MVT::i32); 0
764 SDLoc DL(N); 0
765 SDValue Zero = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32); 0
766 SDNode *R = nullptr; 0
767 ----
768 // Use PS_fi when: ----
769 // - the object is fixed, or ----
770 // - there are no objects with higher-than-default alignment, or ----
771 // - there are no dynamically allocated objects. ----
772 // Otherwise, use PS_fia. ----
773 if (FX < 0 || MaxA <= StkA || !MFI.hasVarSizedObjects()) { 0
774 R = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Hexagon::PS_fi, DL, MVT::i32, FI, Zero); 0
775 } else { ----
776 auto &HMFI = *MF->getInfo(); 0
777 Register AR = HMFI.getStackAlignBaseReg(); 0
778 SDValue CH = CurDAG->getEntryNode(); 0
779 SDValue Ops[] = { CurDAG->getCopyFromReg(CH, DL, AR, MVT::i32), FI, Zero }; 0
780 R = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Hexagon::PS_fia, DL, MVT::i32, Ops); 0
781 } ----
782 ----
783 ReplaceNode(N, R); 0
784 } 0

786 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectAddSubCarry(SDNode *N) { 0
787 unsigned OpcCarry = N->getOpcode() == HexagonISD::ADDC ? Hexagon::A4_addp_c 0
788 : Hexagon::A4_subp_c; 0
789 SDNode *C = CurDAG->getMachineNode(OpcCarry, SDLoc(N), N->getVTList(), 0
790 { N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1), 0
791 N->getOperand(2) }); 0
792 ReplaceNode(N, C); 0
793 } 0
794 ----
795 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectVAlign(SDNode *N) { 0
796 MVT ResTy = N->getValueType(0).getSimpleVT(); 0
797 if (HST->isHVXVectorType(ResTy, true)) 0
798 return SelectHvxVAlign(N); 0
799 ----
800 const SDLoc &dl(N); 0
801 unsigned VecLen = ResTy.getSizeInBits(); 0
802 if (VecLen == 32) { 0
803 SDValue Ops[] = { ----
804 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClassID, dl, MVT::i32), 0
805 N->getOperand(0), 0
806 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Hexagon::isub_hi, dl, MVT::i32), 0
807 N->getOperand(1), 0
808 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Hexagon::isub_lo, dl, MVT::i32) 0
809 }; 0
810 SDNode *R = CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE, dl, 0
811 MVT::i64, Ops); ----
812 ----
813 // Shift right by "(Addr & 0x3) * 8" bytes. ----
814 SDNode *C; ----
815 SDValue M0 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0x18, dl, MVT::i32); 0
816 SDValue M1 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0x03, dl, MVT::i32); 0
817 if (HST->useCompound()) { 0
818 C = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Hexagon::S4_andi_asl_ri, dl, MVT::i32, 0
819 M0, N->getOperand(2), M1); 0
820 } else { ----
821 SDNode *T = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Hexagon::S2_asl_i_r, dl, MVT::i32, 0
822 N->getOperand(2), M1); 0
823 C = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Hexagon::A2_andir, dl, MVT::i32, 0
824 SDValue(T, 0), M0); ----
825 } ----
826 SDNode *S = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Hexagon::S2_lsr_r_p, dl, MVT::i64, 0
827 SDValue(R, 0), SDValue(C, 0)); ----
828 SDValue E = CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(Hexagon::isub_lo, dl, ResTy, 0
829 SDValue(S, 0)); ----
830 ReplaceNode(N, E.getNode()); 0
831 } else { ----
832 assert(VecLen == 64); 0
833 SDNode *Pu = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Hexagon::C2_tfrrp, dl, MVT::v8i1, 0
834 N->getOperand(2)); 0
835 SDNode *VA = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Hexagon::S2_valignrb, dl, ResTy, 0
836 N->getOperand(0), N->getOperand(1), 0
837 SDValue(Pu,0)); ----
838 ReplaceNode(N, VA); 0
839 } ----
840 } 0
841 ----
842 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectVAlignAddr(SDNode *N) { 0
843 const SDLoc &dl(N); 0
844 SDValue A = N->getOperand(1); 0
845 int Mask = -cast(A.getNode())->getSExtValue(); 0
846 assert(isPowerOf2_32(-Mask)); 0
847 ----
848 SDValue M = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Mask, dl, MVT::i32); 0
849 SDNode *AA = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Hexagon::A2_andir, dl, MVT::i32, 0
850 N->getOperand(0), M); 0
851 ReplaceNode(N, AA); 0
852 } 0

863 } 0

907 ----
908 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::Select(SDNode *N) { 0
909 if (N->isMachineOpcode()) 0
910 return N->setNodeId(-1); // Already selected. 0
911 ----
912 auto isHvxOp = [this](SDNode *N) { 0
913 for (unsigned i = 0, e = N->getNumValues(); i != e; ++i) { 0
914 if (HST->isHVXVectorType(N->getValueType(i), true)) 0
915 return true; 0
916 } ----
917 for (SDValue I : N->ops()) { 0
918 if (HST->isHVXVectorType(I.getValueType(), true)) 0
919 return true; 0
920 } ----
921 return false; 0
922 }; 0
923 ----
924 if (HST->useHVXOps() && isHvxOp(N)) { 0
925 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
926 case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: return SelectHvxExtractSubvector(N); 0
927 case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE: return SelectHvxShuffle(N); 0
928 ----
929 case HexagonISD::VROR: return SelectHvxRor(N); 0
930 } ----
931 } ----
932 ----
933 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
934 case ISD::Constant: return SelectConstant(N); 0
935 case ISD::ConstantFP: return SelectConstantFP(N); 0
936 case ISD::FrameIndex: return SelectFrameIndex(N); 0
937 case ISD::SHL: return SelectSHL(N); 0
938 case ISD::LOAD: return SelectLoad(N); 0
939 case ISD::STORE: return SelectStore(N); 0
940 case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN: return SelectIntrinsicWChain(N); 0
941 case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN: return SelectIntrinsicWOChain(N); 0
942 case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: return SelectExtractSubvector(N); 0
943 ----
944 case HexagonISD::ADDC: 0
945 case HexagonISD::SUBC: return SelectAddSubCarry(N); 0
946 case HexagonISD::VALIGN: return SelectVAlign(N); 0
947 case HexagonISD::VALIGNADDR: return SelectVAlignAddr(N); 0
948 case HexagonISD::TYPECAST: return SelectTypecast(N); 0
949 case HexagonISD::P2D: return SelectP2D(N); 0
950 case HexagonISD::D2P: return SelectD2P(N); 0
951 case HexagonISD::Q2V: return SelectQ2V(N); 0
952 case HexagonISD::V2Q: return SelectV2Q(N); 0
953 } ----
954 ----
955 SelectCode(N); 0
956 } ----
957 ----
958 bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel:: 0
959 SelectInlineAsmMemoryOperand(const SDValue &Op, unsigned ConstraintID, ----
960 std::vector &OutOps) { ----
961 SDValue Inp = Op, Res; 0
962 ----
963 switch (ConstraintID) { 0
964 default: 0
965 return true; 0
966 case InlineAsm::Constraint_o: // Offsetable. 0
967 case InlineAsm::Constraint_v: // Not offsetable. ----
968 case InlineAsm::Constraint_m: // Memory. ----
969 if (SelectAddrFI(Inp, Res)) 0
970 OutOps.push_back(Res); 0
971 else ----
972 OutOps.push_back(Inp); 0
973 break; 0
974 } ----
975 ----
976 OutOps.push_back(CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, SDLoc(Op), MVT::i32)); 0
977 return false; 0
978 } ----
979 ----
980 ----
981 static bool isMemOPCandidate(SDNode *I, SDNode *U) { 0
982 // I is an operand of U. Check if U is an arithmetic (binary) operation ----
983 // usable in a memop, where the other operand is a loaded value, and the ----
984 // result of U is stored in the same location. ----
985 ----
986 if (!U->hasOneUse()) 0
987 return false; 0
988 unsigned Opc = U->getOpcode(); 0
989 switch (Opc) { 0
990 case ISD::ADD: 0
991 case ISD::SUB: ----
992 case ISD::AND: ----
993 case ISD::OR: ----
994 break; 0
995 default: 0
996 return false; 0
997 } ----
998 ----
999 SDValue S0 = U->getOperand(0); 0
1000 SDValue S1 = U->getOperand(1); 0
1001 SDValue SY = (S0.getNode() == I) ? S1 : S0; 0
1002 ----
1003 SDNode *UUse = *U->use_begin(); 0
1004 if (UUse->getNumValues() != 1) 0
1005 return false; 0
1006 ----
1007 // Check if one of the inputs to U is a load instruction and the output ----
1008 // is used by a store instruction. If so and they also have the same ----
1009 // base pointer, then don't preoprocess this node sequence as it ----
1010 // can be matched to a memop. ----
1011 SDNode *SYNode = SY.getNode(); 0
1012 if (UUse->getOpcode() == ISD::STORE && SYNode->getOpcode() == ISD::LOAD) { 0
1013 SDValue LDBasePtr = cast(SYNode)->getBasePtr(); 0
1014 SDValue STBasePtr = cast(UUse)->getBasePtr(); 0
1015 if (LDBasePtr == STBasePtr) 0
1016 return true; 0
1017 } ----
1018 return false; 0
1019 } ----
1020 ----
1021 ----
1022 // Transform: (or (select c x 0) z) -> (select c (or x z) z) ----
1023 // (or (select c 0 y) z) -> (select c z (or y z)) ----
1024 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::ppSimplifyOrSelect0(std::vector &&Nodes) { 0
1025 SelectionDAG &DAG = *CurDAG; 0
1026 ----
1027 for (auto *I : Nodes) { 0
1028 if (I->getOpcode() != ISD::OR) 0
1029 continue; 0
1030 ----
1031 auto IsZero = [] (const SDValue &V) -> bool { 0
1032 if (ConstantSDNode *SC = dyn_cast(V.getNode())) 0
1033 return SC->isZero(); 0
1034 return false; 0
1035 }; ----
1036 auto IsSelect0 = [IsZero] (const SDValue &Op) -> bool { 0
1037 if (Op.getOpcode() != ISD::SELECT) 0
1038 return false; 0
1039 return IsZero(Op.getOperand(1)) || IsZero(Op.getOperand(2)); 0
1040 }; ----
1041 ----
1042 SDValue N0 = I->getOperand(0), N1 = I->getOperand(1); 0
1043 EVT VT = I->getValueType(0); 0
1044 bool SelN0 = IsSelect0(N0); 0
1045 SDValue SOp = SelN0 ? N0 : N1; 0
1046 SDValue VOp = SelN0 ? N1 : N0; 0
1047 ----
1048 if (SOp.getOpcode() == ISD::SELECT && SOp.getNode()->hasOneUse()) { 0
1049 SDValue SC = SOp.getOperand(0); 0
1050 SDValue SX = SOp.getOperand(1); 0
1051 SDValue SY = SOp.getOperand(2); 0
1052 SDLoc DLS = SOp; 0
1053 if (IsZero(SY)) { 0
1054 SDValue NewOr = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DLS, VT, SX, VOp); 0
1055 SDValue NewSel = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DLS, VT, SC, NewOr, VOp); 0
1056 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesWith(I, NewSel.getNode()); 0
1057 } else if (IsZero(SX)) { 0
1058 SDValue NewOr = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, DLS, VT, SY, VOp); 0
1059 SDValue NewSel = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, DLS, VT, SC, VOp, NewOr); 0
1060 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesWith(I, NewSel.getNode()); 0
1061 } ----
1062 } 0
1063 } ----
1064 } 0
1065 ----
1066 // Transform: (store ch val (add x (add (shl y c) e))) ----
1067 // to: (store ch val (add x (shl (add y d) c))), ----
1068 // where e = (shl d c) for some integer d. ----
1069 // The purpose of this is to enable generation of loads/stores with ----
1070 // shifted addressing mode, i.e. mem(x+y<<#c). For that, the shift ----
1071 // value c must be 0, 1 or 2. ----
1072 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::ppAddrReorderAddShl(std::vector &&Nodes) { 0
1073 SelectionDAG &DAG = *CurDAG; 0
1074 ----
1075 for (auto *I : Nodes) { 0
1076 if (I->getOpcode() != ISD::STORE) 0
1077 continue; 0
1078 ----
1079 // I matched: (store ch val Off) ----
1080 SDValue Off = I->getOperand(2); 0
1081 // Off needs to match: (add x (add (shl y c) (shl d c)))) ----
1082 if (Off.getOpcode() != ISD::ADD) 0
1083 continue; 0
1084 // Off matched: (add x T0) ----
1085 SDValue T0 = Off.getOperand(1); 0
1086 // T0 needs to match: (add T1 T2): ----
1087 if (T0.getOpcode() != ISD::ADD) 0
1088 continue; 0
1089 // T0 matched: (add T1 T2) ----
1090 SDValue T1 = T0.getOperand(0); 0
1091 SDValue T2 = T0.getOperand(1); 0
1092 // T1 needs to match: (shl y c) ----
1093 if (T1.getOpcode() != ISD::SHL) 0
1094 continue; 0
1095 SDValue C = T1.getOperand(1); 0
1096 ConstantSDNode *CN = dyn_cast(C.getNode()); 0
1097 if (CN == nullptr) 0
1098 continue; 0
1099 unsigned CV = CN->getZExtValue(); 0
1100 if (CV > 2) 0
1101 continue; 0
1102 // T2 needs to match e, where e = (shl d c) for some d. ----
1103 ConstantSDNode *EN = dyn_cast(T2.getNode()); 0
1104 if (EN == nullptr) 0
1105 continue; 0
1106 unsigned EV = EN->getZExtValue(); 0
1107 if (EV % (1 << CV) != 0) 0
1108 continue; 0
1109 unsigned DV = EV / (1 << CV); 0
1110 ----
1111 // Replace T0 with: (shl (add y d) c) ----
1112 SDLoc DL = SDLoc(I); 0
1113 EVT VT = T0.getValueType(); 0
1114 SDValue D = DAG.getConstant(DV, DL, VT); 0
1115 // NewAdd = (add y d) ----
1116 SDValue NewAdd = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, VT, T1.getOperand(0), D); 0
1117 // NewShl = (shl NewAdd c) ----
1118 SDValue NewShl = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, DL, VT, NewAdd, C); 0
1119 ReplaceNode(T0.getNode(), NewShl.getNode()); 0
1120 } 0
1121 } 0
1122 ----
1123 // Transform: (load ch (add x (and (srl y c) Mask))) ----
1124 // to: (load ch (add x (shl (srl y d) d-c))) ----
1125 // where ----
1126 // Mask = 00..0 111..1 0.0 ----
1127 // | | +-- d-c 0s, and d-c is 0, 1 or 2. ----
1128 // | +-------- 1s ----
1129 // +-------------- at most c 0s ----
1130 // Motivating example: ----
1131 // DAG combiner optimizes (add x (shl (srl y 5) 2)) ----
1132 // to (add x (and (srl y 3) 1FFFFFFC)) ----
1133 // which results in a constant-extended and(##...,lsr). This transformation ----
1134 // undoes this simplification for cases where the shl can be folded into ----
1135 // an addressing mode. ----
1136 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::ppAddrRewriteAndSrl(std::vector &&Nodes) { 0
1137 SelectionDAG &DAG = *CurDAG; 0
1138 ----
1139 for (SDNode *N : Nodes) { 0
1140 unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode(); 0
1141 if (Opc != ISD::LOAD && Opc != ISD::STORE) 0
1142 continue; 0
1143 SDValue Addr = Opc == ISD::LOAD ? N->getOperand(1) : N->getOperand(2); 0
1144 // Addr must match: (add x T0) ----
1145 if (Addr.getOpcode() != ISD::ADD) 0
1146 continue; 0
1147 SDValue T0 = Addr.getOperand(1); 0
1148 // T0 must match: (and T1 Mask) ----
1149 if (T0.getOpcode() != ISD::AND) 0
1150 continue; 0
1151 ----
1152 // We have an AND. ----
1153 // ----
1154 // Check the first operand. It must be: (srl y c). ----
1155 SDValue S = T0.getOperand(0); 0
1156 if (S.getOpcode() != ISD::SRL) 0
1157 continue; 0
1158 ConstantSDNode *SN = dyn_cast(S.getOperand(1).getNode()); 0
1159 if (SN == nullptr) 0
1160 continue; 0
1161 if (SN->getAPIntValue().getBitWidth() != 32) 0
1162 continue; 0
1163 uint32_t CV = SN->getZExtValue(); 0
1164 ----
1165 // Check the second operand: the supposed mask. ----
1166 ConstantSDNode *MN = dyn_cast(T0.getOperand(1).getNode()); 0
1167 if (MN == nullptr) 0
1168 continue; 0
1169 if (MN->getAPIntValue().getBitWidth() != 32) 0
1170 continue; 0
1171 uint32_t Mask = MN->getZExtValue(); 0
1172 // Examine the mask. ----
1173 uint32_t TZ = llvm::countr_zero(Mask); 0
1174 uint32_t M1 = llvm::countr_one(Mask >> TZ); 0
1175 uint32_t LZ = llvm::countl_zero(Mask); 0
1176 // Trailing zeros + middle ones + leading zeros must equal the width. ----
1177 if (TZ + M1 + LZ != 32) 0
1178 continue; 0
1179 // The number of trailing zeros will be encoded in the addressing mode. ----
1180 if (TZ > 2) 0
1181 continue; 0
1182 // The number of leading zeros must be at most c. ----
1183 if (LZ > CV) 0
1184 continue; 0
1185 ----
1186 // All looks good. ----
1187 SDValue Y = S.getOperand(0); 0
1188 EVT VT = Addr.getValueType(); 0
1189 SDLoc dl(S); 0
1190 // TZ = D-C, so D = TZ+C. ----
1191 SDValue D = DAG.getConstant(TZ+CV, dl, VT); 0
1192 SDValue DC = DAG.getConstant(TZ, dl, VT); 0
1193 SDValue NewSrl = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, VT, Y, D); 0
1194 SDValue NewShl = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, VT, NewSrl, DC); 0
1195 ReplaceNode(T0.getNode(), NewShl.getNode()); 0
1196 } 0
1197 } 0
1198 ----
1199 // Transform: (op ... (zext i1 c) ...) -> (select c (op ... 0 ...) ----
1200 // (op ... 1 ...)) ----
1201 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::ppHoistZextI1(std::vector &&Nodes) { 0
1202 SelectionDAG &DAG = *CurDAG; 0
1203 ----
1204 for (SDNode *N : Nodes) { 0
1205 unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode(); 0
1206 if (Opc != ISD::ZERO_EXTEND) 0
1207 continue; 0
1208 SDValue OpI1 = N->getOperand(0); 0
1209 EVT OpVT = OpI1.getValueType(); 0
1210 if (!OpVT.isSimple() || OpVT.getSimpleVT() != MVT::i1) 0
1211 continue; 0
1212 for (auto I = N->use_begin(), E = N->use_end(); I != E; ++I) { 0
1213 SDNode *U = *I; 0
1214 if (U->getNumValues() != 1) 0
1215 continue; 0
1216 EVT UVT = U->getValueType(0); 0
1217 if (!UVT.isSimple() || !UVT.isInteger() || UVT.getSimpleVT() == MVT::i1) 0
1218 continue; 0
1219 // Do not generate select for all i1 vector type. ----
1220 if (UVT.isVector() && UVT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1) 0
1221 continue; 0
1222 if (isMemOPCandidate(N, U)) 0
1223 continue; 0
1224 ----
1225 // Potentially simplifiable operation. ----
1226 unsigned I1N = I.getOperandNo(); 0
1227 SmallVector Ops(U->getNumOperands()); 0
1228 for (unsigned i = 0, n = U->getNumOperands(); i != n; ++i) 0
1229 Ops[i] = U->getOperand(i); 0
1230 EVT BVT = Ops[I1N].getValueType(); 0
1231 ----
1232 const SDLoc &dl(U); 0
1233 SDValue C0 = DAG.getConstant(0, dl, BVT); 0
1234 SDValue C1 = DAG.getConstant(1, dl, BVT); 0
1235 SDValue If0, If1; 0
1236 ----
1237 if (isa(U)) { 0
1238 unsigned UseOpc = U->getMachineOpcode(); 0
1239 Ops[I1N] = C0; 0
1240 If0 = SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(UseOpc, dl, UVT, Ops), 0); 0
1241 Ops[I1N] = C1; 0
1242 If1 = SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(UseOpc, dl, UVT, Ops), 0); 0
1243 } else { ----
1244 unsigned UseOpc = U->getOpcode(); 0
1245 Ops[I1N] = C0; 0
1246 If0 = DAG.getNode(UseOpc, dl, UVT, Ops); 0
1247 Ops[I1N] = C1; 0
1248 If1 = DAG.getNode(UseOpc, dl, UVT, Ops); 0
1249 } ----
1250 // We're generating a SELECT way after legalization, so keep the types ----
1251 // simple. ----
1252 unsigned UW = UVT.getSizeInBits(); 0
1253 EVT SVT = (UW == 32 || UW == 64) ? MVT::getIntegerVT(UW) : UVT; 0
1254 SDValue Sel = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, dl, SVT, OpI1, 0
1255 DAG.getBitcast(SVT, If1), ----
1256 DAG.getBitcast(SVT, If0)); ----
1257 SDValue Ret = DAG.getBitcast(UVT, Sel); 0
1258 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesWith(U, Ret.getNode()); 0
1259 } 0
1260 } ----
1261 } 0
1262 ----
1263 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::PreprocessISelDAG() { 0
1264 // Repack all nodes before calling each preprocessing function, ----
1265 // because each of them can modify the set of nodes. ----
1266 auto getNodes = [this]() -> std::vector { 0
1267 std::vector T; 0
1268 T.reserve(CurDAG->allnodes_size()); 0
1269 for (SDNode &N : CurDAG->allnodes()) 0
1270 T.push_back(&N); 0
1271 return T; 0
1272 }; 0
1273 ----
1274 if (HST->useHVXOps()) 0
1275 PreprocessHvxISelDAG(); 0
1276 ----
1277 // Transform: (or (select c x 0) z) -> (select c (or x z) z) ----
1278 // (or (select c 0 y) z) -> (select c z (or y z)) ----
1279 ppSimplifyOrSelect0(getNodes()); 0
1280 ----
1281 // Transform: (store ch val (add x (add (shl y c) e))) ----
1282 // to: (store ch val (add x (shl (add y d) c))), ----
1283 // where e = (shl d c) for some integer d. ----
1284 // The purpose of this is to enable generation of loads/stores with ----
1285 // shifted addressing mode, i.e. mem(x+y<<#c). For that, the shift ----
1286 // value c must be 0, 1 or 2. ----
1287 ppAddrReorderAddShl(getNodes()); 0
1288 ----
1289 // Transform: (load ch (add x (and (srl y c) Mask))) ----
1290 // to: (load ch (add x (shl (srl y d) d-c))) ----
1291 // where ----
1292 // Mask = 00..0 111..1 0.0 ----
1293 // | | +-- d-c 0s, and d-c is 0, 1 or 2. ----
1294 // | +-------- 1s ----
1295 // +-------------- at most c 0s ----
1296 // Motivating example: ----
1297 // DAG combiner optimizes (add x (shl (srl y 5) 2)) ----
1298 // to (add x (and (srl y 3) 1FFFFFFC)) ----
1299 // which results in a constant-extended and(##...,lsr). This transformation ----
1300 // undoes this simplification for cases where the shl can be folded into ----
1301 // an addressing mode. ----
1302 ppAddrRewriteAndSrl(getNodes()); 0
1303 ----
1304 // Transform: (op ... (zext i1 c) ...) -> (select c (op ... 0 ...) ----
1305 // (op ... 1 ...)) ----
1306 ppHoistZextI1(getNodes()); 0
1307 ----
1308 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("isel", { 0
1309 dbgs() << "Preprocessed (Hexagon) selection DAG:"; ----
1310 CurDAG->dump(); ----
1311 }); ----
1312 ----
1313 if (EnableAddressRebalancing) { 0
1314 rebalanceAddressTrees(); 0
1315 ----
1316 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("isel", { 0
1317 dbgs() << "Address tree balanced selection DAG:"; ----
1318 CurDAG->dump(); ----
1319 }); ----
1320 } ----
1321 } 0
1322 ----
1323 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::emitFunctionEntryCode() { 0
1324 auto &HST = MF->getSubtarget(); 0
1325 auto &HFI = *HST.getFrameLowering(); 0
1326 if (!HFI.needsAligna(*MF)) 0
1327 return; 0
1328 ----
1329 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF->getFrameInfo(); 0
1330 MachineBasicBlock *EntryBB = &MF->front(); 0
1331 Align EntryMaxA = MFI.getMaxAlign(); 0
1332 ----
1333 // Reserve the first non-volatile register. ----
1334 Register AP = 0; 0
1335 auto &HRI = *HST.getRegisterInfo(); 0
1336 BitVector Reserved = HRI.getReservedRegs(*MF); 0
1337 for (const MCPhysReg *R = HRI.getCalleeSavedRegs(MF); *R; ++R) { 0
1338 if (Reserved[*R]) 0
1339 continue; 0
1340 AP = *R; 0
1341 break; 0
1342 } ----
1343 assert(AP.isValid() && "Couldn't reserve stack align register"); 0
1344 BuildMI(EntryBB, DebugLoc(), HII->get(Hexagon::PS_aligna), AP) 0
1345 .addImm(EntryMaxA.value()); 0
1346 MF->getInfo()->setStackAlignBaseReg(AP); 0
1347 } 0
1348 ----
1349 void HexagonDAGToDAGISel::updateAligna() { 0
1350 auto &HFI = *MF->getSubtarget().getFrameLowering(); 0
1351 if (!HFI.needsAligna(*MF)) 0
1352 return; 0
1353 auto *AlignaI = const_cast(HFI.getAlignaInstr(*MF)); 0
1354 assert(AlignaI != nullptr); 0
1355 unsigned MaxA = MF->getFrameInfo().getMaxAlign().value(); 0
1356 if (AlignaI->getOperand(1).getImm() < MaxA) 0
1357 AlignaI->getOperand(1).setImm(MaxA); 0
1358 } ----
1359 ----
1360 // Match a frame index that can be used in an addressing mode. ----
1361 bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectAddrFI(SDValue &N, SDValue &R) { 0
1362 if (N.getOpcode() != ISD::FrameIndex) 0
1363 return false; 0
1364 auto &HFI = *HST->getFrameLowering(); 0
1365 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF->getFrameInfo(); 0
1366 int FX = cast(N)->getIndex(); 0
1367 if (!MFI.isFixedObjectIndex(FX) && HFI.needsAligna(*MF)) 0
1368 return false; 0
1369 R = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(FX, MVT::i32); 0
1370 return true; 0
1371 } ----
1372 ----
1373 inline bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectAddrGA(SDValue &N, SDValue &R) { ----
1374 return SelectGlobalAddress(N, R, false, Align(1)); ----
1375 } ----
1376 ----
1377 inline bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectAddrGP(SDValue &N, SDValue &R) { 0
1378 return SelectGlobalAddress(N, R, true, Align(1)); 0
1379 } ----
1380 ----
1381 inline bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectAnyImm(SDValue &N, SDValue &R) { 0
1382 return SelectAnyImmediate(N, R, Align(1)); 0
1383 } ----
1384 ----
1385 inline bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectAnyImm0(SDValue &N, SDValue &R) { 0
1386 return SelectAnyImmediate(N, R, Align(1)); 0
1387 } ----
1388 inline bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectAnyImm1(SDValue &N, SDValue &R) { 0
1389 return SelectAnyImmediate(N, R, Align(2)); 0
1390 } ----
1391 inline bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectAnyImm2(SDValue &N, SDValue &R) { 0
1392 return SelectAnyImmediate(N, R, Align(4)); 0
1393 } ----
1394 inline bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectAnyImm3(SDValue &N, SDValue &R) { 0
1395 return SelectAnyImmediate(N, R, Align(8)); 0
1396 } ----
1397 ----
1398 inline bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectAnyInt(SDValue &N, SDValue &R) { 0
1399 EVT T = N.getValueType(); 0
1400 if (!T.isInteger() || T.getSizeInBits() != 32 || !isa(N)) 0
1401 return false; 0
1402 int32_t V = cast(N)->getZExtValue(); 0
1403 R = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(V, SDLoc(N), N.getValueType()); 0
1404 return true; 0
1405 } ----
1406 ----
1407 bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectAnyImmediate(SDValue &N, SDValue &R, 0
1408 Align Alignment) { ----
1409 switch (N.getOpcode()) { 0
1410 case ISD::Constant: { 0
1411 if (N.getValueType() != MVT::i32) 0
1412 return false; 0
1413 int32_t V = cast(N)->getZExtValue(); 0
1414 if (!isAligned(Alignment, V)) 0
1415 return false; 0
1416 R = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(V, SDLoc(N), N.getValueType()); 0
1417 return true; 0
1418 } ----
1419 case HexagonISD::JT: 0
1420 case HexagonISD::CP: ----
1421 // These are assumed to always be aligned at least 8-byte boundary. ----
1422 if (Alignment > Align(8)) 0
1423 return false; 0
1424 R = N.getOperand(0); 0
1425 return true; 0
1426 case ISD::ExternalSymbol: 0
1427 // Symbols may be aligned at any boundary. ----
1428 if (Alignment > Align(1)) 0
1429 return false; 0
1430 R = N; 0
1431 return true; 0
1432 case ISD::BlockAddress: 0
1433 // Block address is always aligned at least 4-byte boundary. ----
1434 if (Alignment > Align(4) || 0
1435 !isAligned(Alignment, cast(N)->getOffset())) 0
1436 return false; 0
1437 R = N; 0
1438 return true; 0
1439 } ----
1440 ----
1441 if (SelectGlobalAddress(N, R, false, Alignment) || 0
1442 SelectGlobalAddress(N, R, true, Alignment)) 0
1443 return true; 0
1444 ----
1445 return false; 0
1446 } ----
1447 ----
1448 bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::SelectGlobalAddress(SDValue &N, SDValue &R, 0
1449 bool UseGP, Align Alignment) { ----
1450 switch (N.getOpcode()) { 0
1451 case ISD::ADD: { 0
1452 SDValue N0 = N.getOperand(0); 0
1453 SDValue N1 = N.getOperand(1); 0
1454 unsigned GAOpc = N0.getOpcode(); 0
1455 if (UseGP && GAOpc != HexagonISD::CONST32_GP) 0
1456 return false; 0
1457 if (!UseGP && GAOpc != HexagonISD::CONST32) 0
1458 return false; 0
1459 if (ConstantSDNode *Const = dyn_cast(N1)) { 0
1460 if (!isAligned(Alignment, Const->getZExtValue())) 0
1461 return false; 0
1462 SDValue Addr = N0.getOperand(0); 0
1463 if (GlobalAddressSDNode *GA = dyn_cast(Addr)) { 0
1464 if (GA->getOpcode() == ISD::TargetGlobalAddress) { 0
1465 uint64_t NewOff = GA->getOffset() + (uint64_t)Const->getSExtValue(); 0
1466 R = CurDAG->getTargetGlobalAddress(GA->getGlobal(), SDLoc(Const), 0
1467 N.getValueType(), NewOff); ----
1468 return true; 0
1469 } ----
1470 } ----
1471 } ----
1472 break; 0
1473 } ----
1474 case HexagonISD::CP: 0
1475 case HexagonISD::JT: ----
1476 case HexagonISD::CONST32: ----
1477 // The operand(0) of CONST32 is TargetGlobalAddress, which is what we ----
1478 // want in the instruction. ----
1479 if (!UseGP) 0
1480 R = N.getOperand(0); 0
1481 return !UseGP; 0
1482 case HexagonISD::CONST32_GP: 0
1483 if (UseGP) 0
1484 R = N.getOperand(0); 0
1485 return UseGP; 0
1486 default: 0
1487 return false; 0
1488 } ----
1489 ----
1490 return false; 0
1491 } ----
1492 ----
1493 bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::DetectUseSxtw(SDValue &N, SDValue &R) { 0
1494 // This (complex pattern) function is meant to detect a sign-extension ----
1495 // i32->i64 on a per-operand basis. This would allow writing single ----
1496 // patterns that would cover a number of combinations of different ways ----
1497 // a sign-extensions could be written. For example: ----
1498 // (mul (DetectUseSxtw x) (DetectUseSxtw y)) -> (M2_dpmpyss_s0 x y) ----
1499 // could match either one of these: ----
1500 // (mul (sext x) (sext_inreg y)) ----
1501 // (mul (sext-load *p) (sext_inreg y)) ----
1502 // (mul (sext_inreg x) (sext y)) ----
1503 // etc. ----
1504 // ----
1505 // The returned value will have type i64 and its low word will ----
1506 // contain the value being extended. The high bits are not specified. ----
1507 // The returned type is i64 because the original type of N was i64, ----
1508 // but the users of this function should only use the low-word of the ----
1509 // result, e.g. ----
1510 // (mul sxtw:x, sxtw:y) -> (M2_dpmpyss_s0 (LoReg sxtw:x), (LoReg sxtw:y)) ----
1511 ----
1512 if (N.getValueType() != MVT::i64) 0
1513 return false; 0
1514 unsigned Opc = N.getOpcode(); 0
1515 switch (Opc) { 0
1516 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND: 0
1517 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: { ----
1518 // sext_inreg has the source type as a separate operand. ----
1519 EVT T = Opc == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND ----
1520 ? N.getOperand(0).getValueType() 0
1521 : cast(N.getOperand(1))->getVT(); 0
1522 unsigned SW = T.getSizeInBits(); 0
1523 if (SW == 32) 0
1524 R = N.getOperand(0); 0
1525 else if (SW < 32) 0
1526 R = N; 0
1527 else ----
1528 return false; 0
1529 break; 0
1530 } ----
1531 case ISD::LOAD: { 0
1532 LoadSDNode *L = cast(N); 0
1533 if (L->getExtensionType() != ISD::SEXTLOAD) 0
1534 return false; 0
1535 // All extending loads extend to i32, so even if the value in ----
1536 // memory is shorter than 32 bits, it will be i32 after the load. ----
1537 if (L->getMemoryVT().getSizeInBits() > 32) 0
1538 return false; 0
1539 R = N; 0
1540 break; 0
1541 } ----
1542 case ISD::SRA: { 0
1543 auto *S = dyn_cast(N.getOperand(1)); 0
1544 if (!S || S->getZExtValue() != 32) 0
1545 return false; 0
1546 R = N; 0
1547 break; 0
1548 } ----
1549 default: 0
1550 return false; 0
1551 } ----
1552 EVT RT = R.getValueType(); 0
1553 if (RT == MVT::i64) 0
1554 return true; 0
1555 assert(RT == MVT::i32); 0
1556 // This is only to produce a value of type i64. Do not rely on the ----
1557 // high bits produced by this. ----
1558 const SDLoc &dl(N); 0
1559 SDValue Ops[] = { ----
1560 CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClassID, dl, MVT::i32), 0
1561 R, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Hexagon::isub_hi, dl, MVT::i32), 0
1562 R, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Hexagon::isub_lo, dl, MVT::i32) 0
1563 }; 0
1564 SDNode *T = CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE, dl, 0
1565 MVT::i64, Ops); ----
1566 R = SDValue(T, 0); 0
1567 return true; 0
1568 } ----
1569 ----
1570 bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::keepsLowBits(const SDValue &Val, unsigned NumBits, 0
1571 SDValue &Src) { ----
1572 unsigned Opc = Val.getOpcode(); 0
1573 switch (Opc) { 0
1574 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND: 0
1575 case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND: ----
1576 case ISD::ANY_EXTEND: { ----
1577 const SDValue &Op0 = Val.getOperand(0); 0
1578 EVT T = Op0.getValueType(); 0
1579 if (T.isInteger() && T.getSizeInBits() == NumBits) { 0
1580 Src = Op0; 0
1581 return true; 0
1582 } ----
1583 break; 0
1584 } ----
1585 case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG: 0
1586 case ISD::AssertSext: ----
1587 case ISD::AssertZext: ----
1588 if (Val.getOperand(0).getValueType().isInteger()) { 0
1589 VTSDNode *T = cast(Val.getOperand(1)); 0
1590 if (T->getVT().getSizeInBits() == NumBits) { 0
1591 Src = Val.getOperand(0); 0
1592 return true; 0
1593 } ----
1594 } ----
1595 break; 0
1596 case ISD::AND: { 0
1597 // Check if this is an AND with NumBits of lower bits set to 1. ----
1598 uint64_t Mask = (1ULL << NumBits) - 1; 0
1599 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(Val.getOperand(0))) { 0
1600 if (C->getZExtValue() == Mask) { 0
1601 Src = Val.getOperand(1); 0
1602 return true; 0
1603 } ----
1604 } ----
1605 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(Val.getOperand(1))) { 0
1606 if (C->getZExtValue() == Mask) { 0
1607 Src = Val.getOperand(0); 0
1608 return true; 0
1609 } ----
1610 } ----
1611 break; 0
1612 } ----
1613 case ISD::OR: 0
1614 case ISD::XOR: { ----
1615 // OR/XOR with the lower NumBits bits set to 0. ----
1616 uint64_t Mask = (1ULL << NumBits) - 1; 0
1617 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(Val.getOperand(0))) { 0
1618 if ((C->getZExtValue() & Mask) == 0) { 0
1619 Src = Val.getOperand(1); 0
1620 return true; 0
1621 } ----
1622 } ----
1623 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(Val.getOperand(1))) { 0
1624 if ((C->getZExtValue() & Mask) == 0) { 0
1625 Src = Val.getOperand(0); 0
1626 return true; 0
1627 } ----
1628 } ----
1629 break; 0
1630 } ----
1631 default: 0
1632 break; 0
1633 } ----
1634 return false; 0
1635 } ----
1636 ----
1637 bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::isAlignedMemNode(const MemSDNode *N) const { 0
1638 return N->getAlign().value() >= N->getMemoryVT().getStoreSize(); 0
1639 } ----
1640 ----
1641 bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::isSmallStackStore(const StoreSDNode *N) const { 0
1642 unsigned StackSize = MF->getFrameInfo().estimateStackSize(*MF); 0
1643 switch (N->getMemoryVT().getStoreSize()) { 0
1644 case 1: 0
1645 return StackSize <= 56; // 1*2^6 - 8 0
1646 case 2: 0
1647 return StackSize <= 120; // 2*2^6 - 8 0
1648 case 4: 0
1649 return StackSize <= 248; // 4*2^6 - 8 0
1650 default: 0
1651 return false; 0
1652 } ----
1653 } ----
1654 ----
1655 // Return true when the given node fits in a positive half word. ----
1656 bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::isPositiveHalfWord(const SDNode *N) const { 0
1657 if (const ConstantSDNode *CN = dyn_cast(N)) { 0
1658 int64_t V = CN->getSExtValue(); 0
1659 return V > 0 && isInt<16>(V); 0
1660 } ----
1661 if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG) { 0
1662 const VTSDNode *VN = dyn_cast(N->getOperand(1)); 0
1663 return VN->getVT().getSizeInBits() <= 16; 0
1664 } ----
1665 return false; 0
1666 } ----
1667 ----
1668 bool HexagonDAGToDAGISel::hasOneUse(const SDNode *N) const { 0
1669 return !CheckSingleUse || N->hasOneUse(); 0
1670 } ----
1671 ----
1672 //////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////// ----
1673 // Rebalancing of address calculation trees ----
1674 ----
1675 static bool isOpcodeHandled(const SDNode *N) { 0
1676 switch (N->getOpcode()) { 0
1677 case ISD::ADD: 0
1678 case ISD::MUL: ----
1679 return true; 0
1680 case ISD::SHL: 0
1681 // We only handle constant shifts because these can be easily flattened ----
1682 // into multiplications by 2^Op1. ----
1683 return isa(N->getOperand(1).getNode()); 0
1684 default: 0
1685 return false; 0
1686 } ----
1687 } ----
1688 ----
1689 /// Return the weight of an SDNode ----
1690 int HexagonDAGToDAGISel::getWeight(SDNode *N) { 0
1691 if (!isOpcodeHandled(N)) 0
1692 return 1; 0
1693 assert(RootWeights.count(N) && "Cannot get weight of unseen root!"); 0
1694 assert(RootWeights[N] != -1 && "Cannot get weight of unvisited root!"); 0
1695 assert(RootWeights[N] != -2 && "Cannot get weight of RAWU'd root!"); 0
1696 return RootWeights[N]; 0
1697 } ----
1698 ----
1699 int HexagonDAGToDAGISel::getHeight(SDNode *N) { 0
1700 if (!isOpcodeHandled(N)) 0
1701 return 0; 0
1702 assert(RootWeights.count(N) && RootWeights[N] >= 0 && 0
1703 "Cannot query height of unvisited/RAUW'd node!"); ----
1704 return RootHeights[N]; 0
1705 } ----
1706 ----
1707 namespace { ----
1708 struct WeightedLeaf { ----
1709 SDValue Value; ----
1710 int Weight; ----
1711 int InsertionOrder; ----
1712 ----
1713 WeightedLeaf() {} 0
1714 ----
1715 WeightedLeaf(SDValue Value, int Weight, int InsertionOrder) : 0
1716 Value(Value), Weight(Weight), InsertionOrder(InsertionOrder) { 0
1717 assert(Weight >= 0 && "Weight must be >= 0"); 0
1718 } 0
1719 ----
1720 static bool Compare(const WeightedLeaf &A, const WeightedLeaf &B) { 0
1721 assert(A.Value.getNode() && B.Value.getNode()); 0
1722 return A.Weight == B.Weight ? 0
1723 (A.InsertionOrder > B.InsertionOrder) : 0
1724 (A.Weight > B.Weight); 0
1725 } ----
1726 }; ----
1727 ----
1728 /// A specialized priority queue for WeigthedLeaves. It automatically folds ----
1729 /// constants and allows removal of non-top elements while maintaining the ----
1730 /// priority order. ----
1731 class LeafPrioQueue { ----
1732 SmallVector Q; ----
1733 bool HaveConst; ----
1734 WeightedLeaf ConstElt; ----
1735 unsigned Opcode; ----
1736 ----
1737 public: ----
1738 bool empty() { ----
1739 return (!HaveConst && Q.empty()); ----
1740 } ----
1741 ----
1742 size_t size() { 0
1743 return Q.size() + HaveConst; 0
1744 } ----
1745 ----
1746 bool hasConst() { 0
1747 return HaveConst; 0
1748 } ----
1749 ----
1750 const WeightedLeaf &top() { 0
1751 if (HaveConst) 0
1752 return ConstElt; 0
1753 return Q.front(); 0
1754 } ----
1755 ----
1756 WeightedLeaf pop() { 0
1757 if (HaveConst) { 0
1758 HaveConst = false; 0
1759 return ConstElt; 0
1760 } ----
1761 std::pop_heap(Q.begin(), Q.end(), WeightedLeaf::Compare); 0
1762 return Q.pop_back_val(); 0
1763 } ----
1764 ----
1765 void push(WeightedLeaf L, bool SeparateConst=true) { 0
1766 if (!HaveConst && SeparateConst && isa(L.Value)) { 0
1767 if (Opcode == ISD::MUL && 0
1768 cast(L.Value)->getSExtValue() == 1) 0
1769 return; 0
1770 if (Opcode == ISD::ADD && 0
1771 cast(L.Value)->getSExtValue() == 0) 0
1772 return; 0
1773 ----
1774 HaveConst = true; 0
1775 ConstElt = L; 0
1776 } else { ----
1777 Q.push_back(L); 0
1778 std::push_heap(Q.begin(), Q.end(), WeightedLeaf::Compare); 0
1779 } ----
1780 } ----
1781 ----
1782 /// Push L to the bottom of the queue regardless of its weight. If L is ----
1783 /// constant, it will not be folded with other constants in the queue. ----
1784 void pushToBottom(WeightedLeaf L) { 0
1785 L.Weight = 1000; 0
1786 push(L, false); 0
1787 } 0
1788 ----
1789 /// Search for a SHL(x, [<=MaxAmount]) subtree in the queue, return the one of ----
1790 /// lowest weight and remove it from the queue. ----
1791 WeightedLeaf findSHL(uint64_t MaxAmount); ----
1792 ----
1793 WeightedLeaf findMULbyConst(); ----
1794 ----
1795 LeafPrioQueue(unsigned Opcode) : 0
1796 HaveConst(false), Opcode(Opcode) { } 0
1797 }; ----
1798 } // end anonymous namespace ----
1799 ----
1800 WeightedLeaf LeafPrioQueue::findSHL(uint64_t MaxAmount) { 0
1801 int ResultPos; ----
1802 WeightedLeaf Result; 0
1803 ----
1804 for (int Pos = 0, End = Q.size(); Pos != End; ++Pos) { 0
1805 const WeightedLeaf &L = Q[Pos]; 0
1806 const SDValue &Val = L.Value; 0
1807 if (Val.getOpcode() != ISD::SHL || 0
1808 !isa(Val.getOperand(1)) || 0
1809 Val.getConstantOperandVal(1) > MaxAmount) 0
1810 continue; 0
1811 if (!Result.Value.getNode() || Result.Weight > L.Weight || 0
1812 (Result.Weight == L.Weight && Result.InsertionOrder > L.InsertionOrder)) 0
1813 { ----
1814 Result = L; 0
1815 ResultPos = Pos; 0
1816 } ----
1817 } ----
1818 ----
1819 if (Result.Value.getNode()) { 0
1820 Q.erase(&Q[ResultPos]); 0
1821 std::make_heap(Q.begin(), Q.end(), WeightedLeaf::Compare); 0
1822 } ----
1823 ----
1824 return Result; 0
1825 } ----
1826 ----
1827 WeightedLeaf LeafPrioQueue::findMULbyConst() { 0
1828 int ResultPos; ----
1829 WeightedLeaf Result; 0
1830 ----
1831 for (int Pos = 0, End = Q.size(); Pos != End; ++Pos) { 0
1832 const WeightedLeaf &L = Q[Pos]; 0
1833 const SDValue &Val = L.Value; 0
1834 if (Val.getOpcode() != ISD::MUL || 0
1835 !isa(Val.getOperand(1)) || 0
1836 Val.getConstantOperandVal(1) > 127) 0
1837 continue; 0
1838 if (!Result.Value.getNode() || Result.Weight > L.Weight || 0
1839 (Result.Weight == L.Weight && Result.InsertionOrder > L.InsertionOrder)) 0
1840 { ----
1841 Result = L; 0
1842 ResultPos = Pos; 0
1843 } ----
1844 } ----
1845 ----
1846 if (Result.Value.getNode()) { 0
1847 Q.erase(&Q[ResultPos]); 0
1848 std::make_heap(Q.begin(), Q.end(), WeightedLeaf::Compare); 0
1849 } ----
1850 ----
1851 return Result; 0
1852 } ----
1853 ----
1854 SDValue HexagonDAGToDAGISel::getMultiplierForSHL(SDNode *N) { 0
1855 uint64_t MulFactor = 1ull << N->getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
1856 return CurDAG->getConstant(MulFactor, SDLoc(N), 0
1857 N->getOperand(1).getValueType()); 0
1858 } ----
1859 ----
1860 /// @returns the value x for which 2^x is a factor of Val ----
1861 static unsigned getPowerOf2Factor(SDValue Val) { 0
1862 if (Val.getOpcode() == ISD::MUL) { 0
1863 unsigned MaxFactor = 0; 0
1864 for (int i = 0; i < 2; ++i) { 0
1865 ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast(Val.getOperand(i)); 0
1866 if (!C) 0
1867 continue; 0
1868 const APInt &CInt = C->getAPIntValue(); 0
1869 if (CInt.getBoolValue()) 0
1870 MaxFactor = CInt.countr_zero(); 0
1871 } ----
1872 return MaxFactor; 0
1873 } ----
1874 if (Val.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) { 0
1875 if (!isa(Val.getOperand(1).getNode())) 0
1876 return 0; 0
1877 return (unsigned) Val.getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
1878 } ----
1879 ----
1880 return 0; 0
1881 } ----
1882 ----
1883 /// @returns true if V>>Amount will eliminate V's operation on its child ----
1884 static bool willShiftRightEliminate(SDValue V, unsigned Amount) { 0
1885 if (V.getOpcode() == ISD::MUL) { 0
1886 SDValue Ops[] = { V.getOperand(0), V.getOperand(1) }; 0
1887 for (int i = 0; i < 2; ++i) 0
1888 if (isa(Ops[i].getNode()) && 0
1889 V.getConstantOperandVal(i) % (1ULL << Amount) == 0) { 0
1890 uint64_t NewConst = V.getConstantOperandVal(i) >> Amount; 0
1891 return (NewConst == 1); 0
1892 } ----
1893 } else if (V.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) { 0
1894 return (Amount == V.getConstantOperandVal(1)); 0
1895 } ----
1896 ----
1897 return false; 0
1898 } ----
1899 ----
1900 SDValue HexagonDAGToDAGISel::factorOutPowerOf2(SDValue V, unsigned Power) { 0
1901 SDValue Ops[] = { V.getOperand(0), V.getOperand(1) }; 0
1902 if (V.getOpcode() == ISD::MUL) { 0
1903 for (int i=0; i < 2; ++i) { 0
1904 if (isa(Ops[i].getNode()) && 0
1905 V.getConstantOperandVal(i) % ((uint64_t)1 << Power) == 0) { 0
1906 uint64_t NewConst = V.getConstantOperandVal(i) >> Power; 0
1907 if (NewConst == 1) 0
1908 return Ops[!i]; 0
1909 Ops[i] = CurDAG->getConstant(NewConst, 0
1910 SDLoc(V), V.getValueType()); 0
1911 break; 0
1912 } ----
1913 } ----
1914 } else if (V.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) { 0
1915 uint64_t ShiftAmount = V.getConstantOperandVal(1); 0
1916 if (ShiftAmount == Power) 0
1917 return Ops[0]; 0
1918 Ops[1] = CurDAG->getConstant(ShiftAmount - Power, 0
1919 SDLoc(V), V.getValueType()); 0
1920 } ----
1921 ----
1922 return CurDAG->getNode(V.getOpcode(), SDLoc(V), V.getValueType(), Ops); 0
1923 } ----
1924 ----
1925 static bool isTargetConstant(const SDValue &V) { 0
1926 return V.getOpcode() == HexagonISD::CONST32 || 0
1927 V.getOpcode() == HexagonISD::CONST32_GP; 0
1928 } ----
1929 ----
1930 unsigned HexagonDAGToDAGISel::getUsesInFunction(const Value *V) { 0
1931 if (GAUsesInFunction.count(V)) 0
1932 return GAUsesInFunction[V]; 0
1933 ----
1934 unsigned Result = 0; 0
1935 const Function &CurF = CurDAG->getMachineFunction().getFunction(); 0
1936 for (const User *U : V->users()) { 0
1937 if (isa(U) && 0
1938 cast(U)->getParent()->getParent() == &CurF) 0
1939 ++Result; 0
1940 } ----
1941 ----
1942 GAUsesInFunction[V] = Result; 0
1943 ----
1944 return Result; 0
1945 } ----
1946 ----
1947 /// Note - After calling this, N may be dead. It may have been replaced by a ----
1948 /// new node, so always use the returned value in place of N. ----
1949 /// ----
1950 /// @returns The SDValue taking the place of N (which could be N if it is ----
1951 /// unchanged) ----
1952 SDValue HexagonDAGToDAGISel::balanceSubTree(SDNode *N, bool TopLevel) { 0
1953 assert(RootWeights.count(N) && "Cannot balance non-root node."); 0
1954 assert(RootWeights[N] != -2 && "This node was RAUW'd!"); 0
1955 assert(!TopLevel || N->getOpcode() == ISD::ADD); 0
1956 ----
1957 // Return early if this node was already visited ----
1958 if (RootWeights[N] != -1) 0
1959 return SDValue(N, 0); 0
1960 ----
1961 assert(isOpcodeHandled(N)); 0
1962 ----
1963 SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0); 0
1964 SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1); 0
1965 ----
1966 // Return early if the operands will remain unchanged or are all roots ----
1967 if ((!isOpcodeHandled(Op0.getNode()) || RootWeights.count(Op0.getNode())) && 0
1968 (!isOpcodeHandled(Op1.getNode()) || RootWeights.count(Op1.getNode()))) { 0
1969 SDNode *Op0N = Op0.getNode(); 0
1970 int Weight; ----
1971 if (isOpcodeHandled(Op0N) && RootWeights[Op0N] == -1) { 0
1972 Weight = getWeight(balanceSubTree(Op0N).getNode()); 0
1973 // Weight = calculateWeight(Op0N); ----
1974 } else ----
1975 Weight = getWeight(Op0N); 0
1976 ----
1977 SDNode *Op1N = N->getOperand(1).getNode(); // Op1 may have been RAUWd 0
1978 if (isOpcodeHandled(Op1N) && RootWeights[Op1N] == -1) { 0
1979 Weight += getWeight(balanceSubTree(Op1N).getNode()); 0
1980 // Weight += calculateWeight(Op1N); ----
1981 } else ----
1982 Weight += getWeight(Op1N); 0
1983 ----
1984 RootWeights[N] = Weight; 0
1985 RootHeights[N] = std::max(getHeight(N->getOperand(0).getNode()), 0
1986 getHeight(N->getOperand(1).getNode())) + 1; 0
1987 ----
1988 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "--> No need to balance root (Weight=" << Weight 0
1989 << " Height=" << RootHeights[N] << "): "); ----
1990 LLVM_DEBUG(N->dump(CurDAG)); 0
1991 ----
1992 return SDValue(N, 0); 0
1993 } ----
1994 ----
1995 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "** Balancing root node: "); 0
1996 LLVM_DEBUG(N->dump(CurDAG)); 0
1997 ----
1998 unsigned NOpcode = N->getOpcode(); 0
1999 ----
2000 LeafPrioQueue Leaves(NOpcode); 0
2001 SmallVector Worklist; 0
2002 Worklist.push_back(SDValue(N, 0)); 0
2003 ----
2004 // SHL nodes will be converted to MUL nodes ----
2005 if (NOpcode == ISD::SHL) 0
2006 NOpcode = ISD::MUL; 0
2007 ----
2008 bool CanFactorize = false; 0
2009 WeightedLeaf Mul1, Mul2; 0
2010 unsigned MaxPowerOf2 = 0; 0
2011 WeightedLeaf GA; 0
2012 ----
2013 // Do not try to factor out a shift if there is already a shift at the tip of ----
2014 // the tree. ----
2015 bool HaveTopLevelShift = false; 0
2016 if (TopLevel && 0
2017 ((isOpcodeHandled(Op0.getNode()) && Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL && 0
2018 Op0.getConstantOperandVal(1) < 4) || 0
2019 (isOpcodeHandled(Op1.getNode()) && Op1.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL && 0
2020 Op1.getConstantOperandVal(1) < 4))) 0
2021 HaveTopLevelShift = true; 0
2022 ----
2023 // Flatten the subtree into an ordered list of leaves; at the same time ----
2024 // determine whether the tree is already balanced. ----
2025 int InsertionOrder = 0; 0
2026 SmallDenseMap NodeHeights; 0
2027 bool Imbalanced = false; 0
2028 int CurrentWeight = 0; 0
2029 while (!Worklist.empty()) { 0
2030 SDValue Child = Worklist.pop_back_val(); 0
2031 ----
2032 if (Child.getNode() != N && RootWeights.count(Child.getNode())) { 0
2033 // CASE 1: Child is a root note ----
2034 ----
2035 int Weight = RootWeights[Child.getNode()]; 0
2036 if (Weight == -1) { 0
2037 Child = balanceSubTree(Child.getNode()); 0
2038 // calculateWeight(Child.getNode()); ----
2039 Weight = getWeight(Child.getNode()); 0
2040 } else if (Weight == -2) { 0
2041 // Whoops, this node was RAUWd by one of the balanceSubTree calls we ----
2042 // made. Our worklist isn't up to date anymore. ----
2043 // Restart the whole process. ----
2044 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "--> Subtree was RAUWd. Restarting...\n"); 0
2045 return balanceSubTree(N, TopLevel); 0
2046 } ----
2047 ----
2048 NodeHeights[Child] = 1; 0
2049 CurrentWeight += Weight; 0
2050 ----
2051 unsigned PowerOf2; ----
2052 if (TopLevel && !CanFactorize && !HaveTopLevelShift && 0
2053 (Child.getOpcode() == ISD::MUL || Child.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) && 0
2054 Child.hasOneUse() && (PowerOf2 = getPowerOf2Factor(Child))) { 0
2055 // Try to identify two factorizable MUL/SHL children greedily. Leave ----
2056 // them out of the priority queue for now so we can deal with them ----
2057 // after. ----
2058 if (!Mul1.Value.getNode()) { 0
2059 Mul1 = WeightedLeaf(Child, Weight, InsertionOrder++); 0
2060 MaxPowerOf2 = PowerOf2; 0
2061 } else { ----
2062 Mul2 = WeightedLeaf(Child, Weight, InsertionOrder++); 0
2063 MaxPowerOf2 = std::min(MaxPowerOf2, PowerOf2); 0
2064 ----
2065 // Our addressing modes can only shift by a maximum of 3 ----
2066 if (MaxPowerOf2 > 3) 0
2067 MaxPowerOf2 = 3; 0
2068 ----
2069 CanFactorize = true; 0
2070 } ----
2071 } else ----
2072 Leaves.push(WeightedLeaf(Child, Weight, InsertionOrder++)); 0
2073 } else if (!isOpcodeHandled(Child.getNode())) { 0
2074 // CASE 2: Child is an unhandled kind of node (e.g. constant) ----
2075 int Weight = getWeight(Child.getNode()); 0
2076 ----
2077 NodeHeights[Child] = getHeight(Child.getNode()); 0
2078 CurrentWeight += Weight; 0
2079 ----
2080 if (isTargetConstant(Child) && !GA.Value.getNode()) 0
2081 GA = WeightedLeaf(Child, Weight, InsertionOrder++); 0
2082 else ----
2083 Leaves.push(WeightedLeaf(Child, Weight, InsertionOrder++)); 0
2084 } else { ----
2085 // CASE 3: Child is a subtree of same opcode ----
2086 // Visit children first, then flatten. ----
2087 unsigned ChildOpcode = Child.getOpcode(); 0
2088 assert(ChildOpcode == NOpcode || 0
2089 (NOpcode == ISD::MUL && ChildOpcode == ISD::SHL)); ----
2090 ----
2091 // Convert SHL to MUL ----
2092 SDValue Op1; 0
2093 if (ChildOpcode == ISD::SHL) 0
2094 Op1 = getMultiplierForSHL(Child.getNode()); 0
2095 else ----
2096 Op1 = Child->getOperand(1); 0
2097 ----
2098 if (!NodeHeights.count(Op1) || !NodeHeights.count(Child->getOperand(0))) { 0
2099 assert(!NodeHeights.count(Child) && "Parent visited before children?"); 0
2100 // Visit children first, then re-visit this node ----
2101 Worklist.push_back(Child); 0
2102 Worklist.push_back(Op1); 0
2103 Worklist.push_back(Child->getOperand(0)); 0
2104 } else { ----
2105 // Back at this node after visiting the children ----
2106 if (std::abs(NodeHeights[Op1] - NodeHeights[Child->getOperand(0)]) > 1) 0
2107 Imbalanced = true; 0
2108 ----
2109 NodeHeights[Child] = std::max(NodeHeights[Op1], 0
2110 NodeHeights[Child->getOperand(0)]) + 1; 0
2111 } ----
2112 } ----
2113 } ----
2114 ----
2115 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "--> Current height=" << NodeHeights[SDValue(N, 0)] 0
2116 << " weight=" << CurrentWeight ----
2117 << " imbalanced=" << Imbalanced << "\n"); ----
2118 ----
2119 // Transform MUL(x, C * 2^Y) + SHL(z, Y) -> SHL(ADD(MUL(x, C), z), Y) ----
2120 // This factors out a shift in order to match memw(a< ----
2121 if (CanFactorize && (willShiftRightEliminate(Mul1.Value, MaxPowerOf2) || 0
2122 willShiftRightEliminate(Mul2.Value, MaxPowerOf2))) { 0
2123 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "--> Found common factor for two MUL children!\n"); 0
2124 int Weight = Mul1.Weight + Mul2.Weight; 0
2125 int Height = std::max(NodeHeights[Mul1.Value], NodeHeights[Mul2.Value]) + 1; 0
2126 SDValue Mul1Factored = factorOutPowerOf2(Mul1.Value, MaxPowerOf2); 0
2127 SDValue Mul2Factored = factorOutPowerOf2(Mul2.Value, MaxPowerOf2); 0
2128 SDValue Sum = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::ADD, SDLoc(N), Mul1.Value.getValueType(), 0
2129 Mul1Factored, Mul2Factored); ----
2130 SDValue Const = CurDAG->getConstant(MaxPowerOf2, SDLoc(N), 0
2131 Mul1.Value.getValueType()); ----
2132 SDValue New = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::SHL, SDLoc(N), Mul1.Value.getValueType(), 0
2133 Sum, Const); ----
2134 NodeHeights[New] = Height; 0
2135 Leaves.push(WeightedLeaf(New, Weight, Mul1.InsertionOrder)); 0
2136 } else if (Mul1.Value.getNode()) { 0
2137 // We failed to factorize two MULs, so now the Muls are left outside the ----
2138 // queue... add them back. ----
2139 Leaves.push(Mul1); 0
2140 if (Mul2.Value.getNode()) 0
2141 Leaves.push(Mul2); 0
2142 CanFactorize = false; 0
2143 } ----
2144 ----
2145 // Combine GA + Constant -> GA+Offset, but only if GA is not used elsewhere ----
2146 // and the root node itself is not used more than twice. This reduces the ----
2147 // amount of additional constant extenders introduced by this optimization. ----
2148 bool CombinedGA = false; 0
2149 if (NOpcode == ISD::ADD && GA.Value.getNode() && Leaves.hasConst() && 0
